Sapindus emarginatus

   [9554.jpg]
    Authority   Vahl.
      Family    Magnoliopsida:Rosidae:Sapindales:Sapindaceae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 9554

   Notes
   SOURCES
   Joshi H 1980a pp 238-240 [TEMP, RAIN, TEXT, DRA, PH, USE]
   KILLING T
   Tolerant to below 2.5Â°C.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial deciduous tree. In India the flowers appear in
   October-December, and fruits ripen in February-May.
   COMMON NAMES
   Ritha, Soapnut tree of South India, Bara-ritha, Aritha, Antala,
   Pasakotto, Rithe, Muktamaya, Phenila, Pounanga, Kurkudu.
   FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonyms: S. trifoliatus, S. laurifolius, S. acutus, S.
   abstergens. Ritha can reach a height of up to 18 m. The tree is found
   at low elevations.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
